00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:36,940
along the various basis vector directions.

333
00:13:36,940 --> 00:13:41,080
So alpha sub i's are the components of the vectors.

334
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:44,800
And I'm interested in the components of the output vector.

335
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:47,320
I would like to know in a

336
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,580
concrete way what are the components of b.

337
00:13:49,740 --> 00:13:50,720
So to find out,

338
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:54,800
I just project them onto the direction i.

339
00:13:59,359 --> 00:14:02,260
a m i.

340
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:04,870
All I've done is in both

341
00:14:04,870 --> 00:14:06,760
sides of the equation project or to,

342
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:07,600
project this to,

343
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:09,400
take the inner product with the vector i.

344
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:13,560
This by definition is beta i.

345
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,060
In other words,

346
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:17,780
if I were to expand b

347
00:14:17,780 --> 00:14:19,500
in the same way I expanded a,

348
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,300
I would use the coefficients beta i.

349
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:24,260
That's what we learned up on the top board.

350
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:25,900
This is beta i.

351
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:26,860
How about over here?

352
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,490
What can I do with this

