00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:05,500
and the output is also a column.

438
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:09,320
It's a column because a was a ket vector

439
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:10,700
and b was a ket vector.

440
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:11,940
All right,

441
00:18:11,940 --> 00:18:13,920
so another way to write the same thing,

442
00:18:14,020 --> 00:18:16,210
this is one way to

443
00:18:16,210 --> 00:18:18,400
write m times a equals b.

444
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:19,880
Well,

445
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:21,060
here's one way to write it,

446
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:21,520
abstract.

447
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,660
Here's another way to write it as a concrete sum,

448
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:27,020
and the third way is to recognize

449
00:18:27,020 --> 00:18:28,740
that this is just the multiplication

450
00:18:28,740 --> 00:18:30,960
of a matrix times a column vector.

451
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:34,540
You write the matrix m

